{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/debut-theme-sticky-navigation-bar-tutorial","result":{"pageContext":{"id":480,"date":"2020-12-15T08:20:00","date_gmt":"2020-12-15T08:20:00","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=480"},"modified":"2021-04-19T18:09:51","modified_gmt":"2021-04-19T18:09:51","slug":"debut-theme-sticky-navigation-bar-tutorial","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/debut-theme-sticky-navigation-bar-tutorial/","title":{"rendered":"Debut Theme: sticky navigation bar tutorial"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Regardless of your business strategy one thing every theme should give you is freedom. Freedom to A/B test whatever does or does not work for you. <br><br>Debut theme, while being an amazing theme, lacks a few essential features, like a sticky navigation bar. In this tutorial I&#8217;ll teach you how to quickly install it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Downloading the files</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Download the files <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/debut-theme-sticky-navbar-pro\" target=\"_blank\">clicking here</a>. (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://debut-theme-slider.myshopify.com/products/blue-silk-tuxedo\" target=\"_blank\">live preview</a>) <br><br>Complete details with all included features can be foundÂ <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/debut-theme-sticky-navbar-pro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Updating the header file</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol id=\"block-dbf1fa37-09f6-4cb3-ad8d-83d260fc44e4\"><li>In your Shopify admin, go to&nbsp;<strong>Online Store</strong>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Themes&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Actions&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Edit Code</strong>.</li><li>Open the <strong>header.txt </strong>file that you downloaded and copy all the code in there.</li><li>Now go back to your Shopify admin, find the <strong>header.liquid</strong> file in your theme.</li><li>Delete everything in there and paste the code that you copied.</li><li>Save. Make sure the first line says &#8220;Sticky Debut Header&#8221; like this:<br><br><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"947\" height=\"709\" class=\"wp-image-188\" style=\"width: 1000px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/firstfile.jpg\" alt=\"Liquid code for Shopify\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/firstfile.jpg 947w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/firstfile-600x449.jpg 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/firstfile-768x575.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 947px) 100vw, 947px\" /></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<h3>Fixing the page jumping bug</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re on mobile and click on &#8220;search&#8221; or the button to expand the menu you may notice that the page will jump up. There is a very easy simple way to fix this:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol id=\"block-f09ca9ff-30e0-46e2-a78c-7e73b2727e8f\"><li>In your Shopify admin, go to&nbsp;<strong>Online Store</strong>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Themes&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Actions&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Edit Code</strong>.</li><li>Find the file <strong>theme.js</strong>.</li><li>Press CTRL +F (or command + F on Mac) and search for <strong>(0, 0) </strong></li><li>Delete this line. Here is how it looks like before and after:</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"879\" height=\"661\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-189\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-4.png 879w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-4-600x451.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-4-768x578.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 879px) 100vw, 879px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"816\" height=\"596\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-5.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-190\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-5.png 816w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-5-600x438.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/image-5-768x561.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 816px) 100vw, 816px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>Now you&#8217;re ready to use your Sticky navigation bar. Happy sales!</p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Add a sticky navigation bar to your theme in under one minute for free and effortlessly. </p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":345,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[154,157,12],"image_alt":"","acf":[],"featured_image_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/debut-sticky-pro-600x338.png","featured_image_small_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/debut-sticky-pro-100x100.png","featured_image_large_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/debut-sticky-pro-1200x675.png","post_count":1,"categories_names":["Blog"],"tag_names":["Code Tutorial","debut theme","product"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/480"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/comments?post=480"}],"version-history":[{"count":10,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/480/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":742,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/480/revisions/742"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media/345"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media?parent=480"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/categori